      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must be directly relevant to the clinical hemolysis prediction objective.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH), directly linked to the clinical endpoint of pump-induced hemolysis. Secondary QoIs include volume-averaged shear stress and exposure time distributions. All QoIs are standard measures in blood damage literature and directly support the COU decision."
    },
    {
